Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 1,620,560.42 and Total Revenue = 2,869,560.42.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
  = (1,620,560.42 / 2,869,560.42) × 100 ≈ 56.49%

Step 2: Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –650,630.22.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities (debt) = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 485,000.00 + 143,478.02 = 628,478.02.
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Debt
  = –650,630.22 / 628,478.02 ≈ –1.04

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "56.49%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-1.04"
  }
}
